Continuation of Therapy Aetna considers continuation of onabotulinumtoxinA (Botox) therapy medically necessary for all members (including new members) requesting reauthorization for an indication listed in Section I.B. (excluding chronic migraine prophylaxis) who meet all initial authorization criteria and are experiencing benefit from therapy. Aetna considers continuation of onabotulinumtoxinA (Botox) therapy medically necessary for treatment of chronic migraine prophylaxis when the member has achieved or maintained a reduction in monthly headache frequency since starting therapy with onabotulinumtoxinA (Botox).

